{"id":45210,"title":"A precordial rub in a boy with a severe attack of ulcerative colitis.","abstract":"A case of a pneumomediastinum mimicking a pericarditis in a boy with an occult perforation due to ulcerative colitis is reported. Pneumomediastinum is a rare complication of severe attacks of ulcerative colitis, with or without the previous development of a toxic megacolon, that should be considered in the differential diagnosis. ","date":"2014-04-03","categories":"Digestive System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24694884","annotations":[{"name":"Differential diagnosis","weight":0.786344,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_diagnosis"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.460335,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.231976,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Ulcerative colitis","weight":0.172222,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ulcerative_colitis"},{"name":"Toxicity","weight":0.159972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toxicity"},{"name":"Colitis","weight":0.118832,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colitis"},{"name":"Occult","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Occult"},{"name":"Megacolon","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Megacolon"},{"name":"Pneumomediastinum","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pneumomediastinum"},{"name":"Pericarditis","weight":0.0287296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pericarditis"},{"name":"Toxic megacolon","weight":0.0287296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toxic_megacolon"},{"name":"Differential (mechanical device)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_(mechanical_device)"},{"name":"Ulcer (dermatology)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"ht